# widget-client/.env.example
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SAFE TO COMMIT — contains no real secrets. Copy this file to .env (for dev)
# or .env.production (for production builds) and fill in the real IP.
#
#   copy .env.example .env              (Windows — local dev)
#   copy .env.example .env.production   (Windows — production build)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Gateway URL ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Base URL of the gateway-service (no trailing slash, no /api/chat suffix).
#
# CRITICAL for intranet deployment: set this to the intranet IP of the machine
# running the gateway-service BEFORE running `npm run build`. The value is
# baked into the compiled JS bundle at build time (via Vite define).
#
# Intranet example:
#   VITE_GATEWAY_URL=http://192.168.1.100:3000
#
# Local dev (default if unset — safe to omit):
#   VITE_GATEWAY_URL=http://localhost:3000
VITE_GATEWAY_URL=http://<GATEWAY_HOST_IP>:3000
